<tr>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;" class=3D"tab-s">&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;">
<p class=3D"bull-s"><a id=3D"page_105"></a><span class=3D"bul-s">=E2=80=A2<=
/span> Often analysis of requirements leads to further elicitation activity=
, as questions arise and need to be investigated further.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;" class=3D"tab-s">Requirements validation</=
td>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;">
<p class=3D"bull-s"><span class=3D"bul-s">=E2=80=A2</span> This stage invol=
ves the review of requirements by interested stakeholders.</p>
<p class=3D"bull-s"><span class=3D"bul-s">=E2=80=A2</span> It includes achi=
eving approval from the sponsor, requirement owners and any other appropria=
tely nominated stakeholders.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;" class=3D"tab-s">Requirements documentatio=
