<p class=3D"bull-s"><span class=3D"bul-s">=E2=80=A2</span> As analysis take=
s place, the requirements document becomes more structured.</p>
<p class=3D"bull-s"><span class=3D"bul-s">=E2=80=A2</span> The =E2=80=98doc=
ument=E2=80=99 may take any number of formats: requirements can be stored i=
n word-processed documents or specific requirements management or computer-=
aided software engineering tools.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"vertical-align:top;" class=3D"tab-s">Requirements management</=
